<p dir="ltr">For those curious, the <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/11662585/hollow-knight/posts/2546388" rel="nofollow ">previous Kickstarter update</a> was a post right after E3 2019 talking about a demo for Hollow Knight: Silksong. Funnily enough, the Gamescom demo playable this week seems to be nearly identical to the experience from E3 2019 (an event that no longer exists). GameSpot did get <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/hollow-knight-silksong-is-real-and-i-played-it/1100-6534147/">hands-on time with Hollow Knight: Silksong at Gamescom</a>.</p><p dir="ltr">Kickstarter backers receiving Hollow Knight: Silksong codes was foreshadowed yesterday when Bloomberg's Jason Schreier posted on social media that <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/hollow-knight-silksong-reviews-probably-arent-going-to-be-ready-for-launch/1100-6534191/">reviews probably wouldn't be ready before the game's launch</a>. That's reportedly because Team Cherry would find it unfair for critics to play the game earlier than original backers.</p><p dir="ltr">The anticipation for Hollow Knight: Silksong's upcoming launch feels pretty tangible. For instance, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/hollow-knight-just-hit-an-all-time-peak-on-steam-after-silksong-release-date-reveal/1100-6534206/">Hollow Knight just hit an all-time concurrent-players peak on Steam</a> with over 22,000 people. In addition, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/silksong-release-date-has-already-prompted-two-game-delays/1100-6534203/">at least three indie games are pushing back their release dates</a> now to avoid coming out near Hollow Knight: Silksong.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
