<p>Hollow Knight's previously Steam concurrent record of around 20,000 players was achieved in May 2022. All of this data comes from <a href="https://steamdb.info/app/367520/charts/#6y" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">SteamDB.</a></p><p>Steam's own sales data shows that <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/charts/topselling/US" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Hollow Knight jumped into the top 50 overall best-selling games</a> on the platform. The game is also available on console platforms, but sales or engagement data is not available. Hollow Knight is also available on <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/best-xbox-game-pass-games/2900-4001/" data-ref-id="2900-4001">Game Pass</a> (and Silksong will be as well).</p><p>At least <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/silksong-release-date-has-already-prompted-two-game-delays/1100-6534203/" data-ref-id="1100-6534203">three games have already been delayed due, in part, to Silksong</a>. The game is set for release on September 4, and it's been a long time coming.</p><p>"Hollow Knight: Silksong appears to be exactly what we all should have expected: a strong, well-designed, visually lovely game that carries forward the aesthetic and design philosophies of the original with thoughtful, if not earth-shattering, updates," GameSpot's Steve Watts wrote after going <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/hollow-knight-silksong-is-real-and-i-played-it/1100-6534147/">hands-on with Silksong at Gamescom this week</a>.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
